      "writtenOn": "2020-01-23T21:37:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "thinking about this a bit more, we must not allow \\\nso that users don\u0027t shoot themselves in the foot by putting Windows-specific paths\n\nnot for this CL",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 40,
        "startChar": 55,
        "endLine": 40,
        "endChar": 60
      },
      "revId": "0c7b82cfa7b1b1e9993c1d0d2dca7a757578e288",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b3b2da59_76f4c477",
        "filename": "resultdb/pbutil/test_result.go",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 40,
      "author": {
        "id": 1147264
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-01-24T11:13:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "As long as the path is unique within the test result, any character can be put?\n\nAccording to the field description in sink.proto, the key of a map{} entry in input_artifacts are copied to the Artifact.Name. It\u0027s not copied from sinkpb.Artifact.FilePath.\n\n```\n  // Equivalent of luci.resultpb.TestResult.input_artifacts.\n  // The map key is an artifact name.\n  map\u003cstring, Artifact\u003e input_artifacts \u003d 10;\n```\n\nAlso, Artifact has field fetch_url. Therefore, Artifact.Name doesn\u0027t need to be embedded into an URL. In my understanding, it is just the unique ID of each Artifact within the TestResult.",
      "parentUuid": "98f60857_58cb6f57",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 40,
        "startChar": 55,
        "endLine": 40,
        "endChar": 60
      },
      "revId": "0c7b82cfa7b1b1e9993c1d0d2dca7a757578e288",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ebb29bff_512440df",
        "filename": "resultdb/pbutil/test_result.go",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 40,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-01-24T19:07:57Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e As long as the path is unique within the test result, any character can be put?\n\nResultDB itself doesn\u0027t care much because it does not interpret artifact names.\nBut customers will suffer if we don\u0027t establish any constraints. Thinking about this a bit more, perhaps this should be limited to valid Unix file paths, so that a generic client could save an artifact on the local filesystem with the same name. On Windows, we will just replace / with \\.",
      "parentUuid": "b3b2da59_76f4c477",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 40,
        "startChar": 55,
        "endLine": 40,
        "endChar": 60
      },
      "revId": "0c7b82cfa7b1b1e9993c1d0d2dca7a757578e288",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
