      "side": 1,
      "message": "I believe that it\u0027s the best to type the field with uint64 in the proto, and patchset#1 of this CL actually included the change.\n\nHowever, it caused a compile error at the following location, and, I reverted the change in the following patchset.\n: https://source.chromium.org/chromium/_/chromium/infra/luci/luci-go/+/ea63c8586eae34954223a1c68834a50ff18c6660:resultdb/cmd/recorder/chromium/util/isolated.go;l\u003d52;drc\u003d52246ef152242716e7c33424aec8e8fc28c01165?originalUrl\u003dhttps:%2F%2Fcs.chromium.org%2F\n\nIt\u0027s basically because Isolate.File.Size is typed as *int64.\n: https://source.chromium.org/chromium/_/chromium/infra/luci/luci-go/+/7c921a504b20af5c83024236f7f09bdb10118377:common/isolated/isolated.go;l\u003d63;drc\u003d1959e6eb61432386b7cf6f69f6bc7bfedc0d2c57?originalUrl\u003dhttps:%2F%2Fcs.chromium.org%2F\n\nI can add a validator such that an Artifact with a negative number in Size becomes invalid. However, then, how should IsolatedFileToArtifact() in recorder handle an input Isolate file, if it has a negative number in Size?",
